text: Jean Hurring (née Stewart, 23 December 1930 – 8 August 2020) was a New Zealand swimmer. She won a bronze medal in the 100 m backstroke at the 1952 Summer Olympics. Stewart was born in Dunedin, New Zealand. Stewart died on 8 August 2020 in Auckland at the age of 89.Jean Stewart ==References== Category:1930 births Category:2020 deaths Category:New Zealand swimmers Category:Olympic bronze medalists for New Zealand
